# =============================================================================
# tests.http — REST Client API Tests
# =============================================================================
# Install "REST Client" by Huachao Mao in VS Code.
# Click "Send Request" above any ### block to fire that HTTP request.
# This file grows with each phase.
# =============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 0 / 1a — Core API
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Health Check — verify the API is running
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### 2. List all documents — should return JSON array
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/

###

### 3. Upload a document (multipart form)
# Replace the file content below with anything — this creates a real upload.
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test-document.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

This is a test document for CogniDocs Phase 1.
When uploaded, this file goes to Azure Blob Storage.
Event Grid then fires a BlobCreated event.
The Azure Function receives the event and publishes to Service Bus.
In Phase 2, the worker will chunk and embed this text.
--boundary123--

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 1b — Azure Function health (after deployment)
# Replace <your-function-app> with your actual Function App name.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4. Check Function App is running
GET https://func-cognidocs.azurewebsites.net/api/health

###
